def _get_grouper(
    obj,
    key=None,
    axis=0,
    level=None,
    sort=True,
    observed=False,
    mutated=False,
    validate=True,
):
    if axis == 0:
        # Perform groupby operation by index
        groupings = [Grouping(group_axis, g, level=level) for g in [key] if key is not None]
        grouper = BaseGrouper(group_axis, groupings, sort=sort)
        return grouper, [], obj
    elif axis == 1:
        # Perform groupby operation by columns
        group_axis = obj.columns
        keys = [key] if isinstance(key, str) else key
        groupings = [Grouping(group_axis, g, level=level) for g in keys]
        grouper = BaseGrouper(group_axis, groupings, sort=sort)
        return grouper, [], obj
    else:
        raise ValueError("Invalid axis value")
